# Inventory Management System

Flask REST API + CLI with OpenFoodFacts integration.

## Setup
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
python app.py
```

## Run Tests
```bash
pytest tests/ -v
```

## API

| Method | Route | Description |
|--------|-------|-------------|
| GET | `/inventory` | Get all items |
| GET | `/inventory/<id>` | Get one item |
| POST | `/inventory` | Add item |
| PATCH | `/inventory/<id>` | Update item |
| DELETE | `/inventory/<id>` | Delete item |
| GET | `/fetch-product?barcode=<code>` | Lookup from OpenFoodFacts |
| GET | `/fetch-product?name=<name>&add=true` | Lookup and save |

## CLI
```bash
python cli.py list
python cli.py get 1
python cli.py add
python cli.py update 2
python cli.py delete 3
python cli.py fetch --barcode 0041196896005
python cli.py fetch --name "almond milk" --add
```